    • Field Detail

      • MARKET_MIRROR_NAME_KEY

        public static final String MARKET_MIRROR_NAME_KEY
        Property that may be added to broken out messages so that the policy engine can access the correct market mirror for a message. The value associated with this key is a string naming the market mirror instance.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • FIX_VERSION_KEY

        public static final String FIX_VERSION_KEY
        Property that may be added to broken out messages so that the policy engine can generate messages for the correct FIX version. The value associated with this key is a standard fix version string (e.g., "FIX.4.4").
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DISPOSITION_NONE

        public static final int DISPOSITION_NONE
        Codes indicating what eventually happened to a broken out message.
        • DISPOSITION_NONE nothing has happened, the message is still in the break out box.
        • DISPOSITION_USER_ACCEPT a user accepted it.
        • DISPOSITION_USER_REJECT a user rejected it.
        • DISPOSITION_USER_RETRY a user retried it.
        • DISPOSITION_CANCELLED was cancelled by another message.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • BrokenOutMessageData

        public BrokenOutMessageData(IFIXMessageProcessor source,
                            int id,
                            Date date,
                            IFIXMessage message,
                            List reasons)
        Construct new BrokenOutMessageData
        Parameters:
        source - the message processor that was the source of this message.
        id - a unique id for this broken out message within the enclosing break out box.
        message - the message to be broken out.
        date - the date and time that the message was broken out
        reasons - a list of reasons (instances of IBreakOutReason) indicating why the message was broken out.
